name: Observe -> Cables,
description: Inspect all the cables, in such a way to access all of their ports. Is a cable terminal disconnected from the relavant port?, outcome='NOMINAL\n\nBased on your systematic inspection of all cable connections, every cable terminal is physically connected to its relevant port, and no signs of anomalous behavior (such as detached or loose connections) were found. No CablesDetached issue is indicated by the reported outcomes. All access actions (inverting enclosures, opening panels) were carried out as needed to expose the ports for inspection, and each connection check succeeded. No further action regarding cable detachment is necessary at this stage.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=100.0, cost_breakdown=[('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
